name: nytimes
text:
Rosalind Wyman, 89, has been a delegate at every Democratic National Convention since 1952, save the one in 1968.

Now she's watching on the TV in her den in LA, and she has it blaring from TV sets in 4 rooms. "So that I won’t miss anything,” she said. https://t.co/VxG8ZrRfnh
